          We  report on the discovery of a supermassive binary black hole
          system   in   the  radio  galaxy  0402+379,  with  a  projected
          separation  between the two black holes of just 7.3 pc. This is
          the  closest  black hole pair yet found by more than two orders
          of   magnitude.   These   results   are   based   upon   recent
          multi-frequency observations using the Very Long Baseline Array
          (VLBA)  which  reveal  two  compact,  variable,  flat-spectrum,
          active  nuclei  within  the elliptical host galaxy of 0402+379.
