          than the correlation between stellar mass and SFR. All galaxies
          in  the  sample  have SFRs per unit area Sigma_SFR in the range
          observed in local starbursts. We compare the instantaneous SFRs
          and the past average SFRs as inferred from the ages and stellar
          masses, finding that for most of the sample, the current SFR is
          an  adequate  representation of the past average. There is some
          evidence  that  the  most massive galaxies (M_star >10^11 Msun)
