          The  recently  started  Arecibo L-band Feed Array (ALFA) pulsar
          survey aims to find ~1000 new pulsars. Due to its high time and
          frequency  resolution  the  survey  is  especially sensitive to
          millisecond   pulsars,   which   have  the  potential  to  test
          gravitational  theories,  detect  gravitational waves and probe
          the  neutron-star equation of state. Here we report the results
          of  our  preliminary  analysis:  in  the  first  months we have
