          emission   features   were  detected.  The  northeast-southwest
          bipolar  outflow driven by IRAS 4A was studied by combining the
          H2  images  with  SiO  maps  published  previously.  The SiO-H2
          outflows are continuous on the southwestern side but show a gap
          on  the northeastern side. The southwestern outflow lobe curves
